\begin_layout Standard
The marker, as it turned out, had a contingency that terminated the current
 restart if 'significant tampering' of the controller's mind or soul is
 detected.
 It was unclear what exactly would qualify as 'significant tampering', but
 apparently even wrenching a soul out of the Controller's body was enough to
 trigger it.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In Zorian's marker, this function was non-functional, which was why he could go
 through Alanic's soul training without any issues.
 Zach's marker, however, was not defective in this manner.
